      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\community-launchpad-proto\\README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # FirstGens Community — Platform Prototype & Blueprint\n2: \n3: > **First-generation university students deserve a community platform that truly understands them.**\n4: > This repository is both the clickable prototype (run it today) *and* the complete technical blueprint for the production Frappe-powered platform it will become.\n5: \n6: ---\n7: \n8: ## Table of Contents\n9: \n10: 1. [What this is](#1-what-this-is)\n11: 2. [What this will become](#2-what-this-will-become)\n12: 3. [Running it right now](#3-running-it-right-now)\n13: 4. [Architecture overview](#4-architecture-overview)\n14: 5. [User journeys — Mermaid flowcharts](#5-user-journeys--mermaid-flowcharts)\n15:    - 5.1 [New member onboarding](#51-new-member-onboarding)\n16:    - 5.2 [Posting in a Space](#52-posting-in-a-space)\n17:    - 5.3 [Mentor match flow](#53-mentor-match-flow)\n18:    - 5.4 [Event RSVP flow](#54-event-rsvp-flow)\n19:    - 5.5 [Course enrolment & progress](#55-course-enrolment--progress)\n20:    - 5.6 [Direct messages (Raven)](#56-direct-messages-raven)\n21:    - 5.7 [Safeguarding & moderation pipeline](#57-safeguarding--moderation-pipeline)\n22:    - 5.8 [Paywall / membership gating](#58-paywall--membership-gating)\n23:    - 5.9 [Gamification & badge award](#59-gamification--badge-award)\n24:    - 5.10 [Weekly community digest](#510-weekly-community-digest)\n25:    - 5.11 [Full platform data flow](#511-full-platform-data-flow)\n26: 6. [Project structure](#6-project-structure)\n27: 7. [Pages & routes](#7-pages--routes)\n28: 8. [Mock data & schema contract](#8-mock-data--schema-contract)\n29: 9. [The Frappe DNA — why this stack](#9-the-frappe-dna--why-this-stack)\n30: 10. [The Circle.so DNA — feature parity map](#10-the-circleso-dna--feature-parity-map)\n31: 11. [Documentation index](#11-documentation-index)\n32: 12. [How long to production?](#12-how-long-to-production)\n33: 13. [Contributing & branch rules](#13-contributing--branch-rules)\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## 1. What this is\n38: \n39: **A high-fidelity, clickable UX/UI prototype** for a community platform supporting first-generation university students in the UK. It exists so stakeholders, designers, and prospective users can:\n40: \n41: - Click through realistic end-to-end flows before a single production database row is written\n42: - Validate the information architecture\n43: - Sign off UX decisions as Gherkin scenarios (see [`docs/09_GHERKIN_UX_SCENARIOS.md`](docs/09_GHERKIN_UX_SCENARIOS.md))\n44: - Confirm that the data model is schema-faithful to the real Frappe backend\n45: \n46: **Tech stack (prototype only):**\n47: \n48: | Layer | Choice | Why |\n49: |---|---|---|\n50: | UI framework | Vue 3 + TypeScript | Type-safe components that mirror Frappe shapes |\n51: | Router | Vue Router 4 | File-based routing, SSR-ready |\n52: | Server | Vite 8 | Fast HMR, production build |\n53: | Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 + frappe-ui | Rapid design-system iteration, Frappe design tokens |\n54: | State / data | In-memory mock store (`src/mock-data/`) | No backend needed for prototype |\n55: | Dev tooling | Node.js, Vite 8, ESLint, Prettier | Fast iteration |\n56: \n57: **Important:** there is no database, no auth, no external API call in this prototype. A full page reload resets all in-memory state to the seeded mock data.\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## 2. What this will become\n62: \n63: The production system will be built on the **Frappe Framework**, composing:\n64: \n65: | App | Role |\n66: |---|---|\n67: | [`frappe/frappe`](https://github.com/frappe/frappe) | Platform: auth, ORM, REST, jobs, audit log |\n68: | [`frappe/gameplan`](https://github.com/frappe/gameplan) | Community: Teams, Spaces (Projects), Posts (Discussions), Comments, Reactions |\n69: | [`frappe/lms`](https://github.com/frappe/lms) | Learning: Courses, Chapters, Lessons, Quizzes, Certificates |\n70: | [`frappe/raven`](https://github.com/The-Commit-Company/Raven) | Direct messaging + channels |\n71: | [`frappe/helpdesk`](https://github.com/frappe/helpdesk) | Member support + safeguarding triage |\n72: | [`frappe/wiki`](https://github.com/frappe/wiki) | Community handbook, code of conduct |\n73: | [`frappe/insights`](https://github.com/frappe/insights) | Analytics dashboards |\n74: | [`frappe/eps`](https://github.com/frappe/eps) | Gamification / Energy Points |\n75: | `fg_companion` *(new, ~1,500 lines Python)* | Events, mentor matching, AI hooks, moderation, polls, badges |\n76: \n77: The prototype's TypeScript types in [`src/mock-data/types.ts`](src/mock-data/types.ts) are **deliberately 1:1 with real Frappe DocType field names**. The porting work is a data-layer swap, not a redesign. See [`docs/03_PORTING_GUIDE.md`](docs/03_PORTING_GUIDE.md) and [`docs/04_FRAPPE_TRANSLATION.md`](docs/04_FRAPPE_TRANSLATION.md).\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## 3. Running it right now\n82: \n83: ### Prerequisites\n84: \n85: | Tool | Minimum version | Check |\n86: |---|---|---|\n87: | [Node.js](https://nodejs.org) | 20 LTS | `node -v` |\n88: | Git | any recent | `git --version` |\n89: \n90: ### Clone & install\n91: \n92: ```bash\n93: git clone https://github.com/andiekobbietks/community-launchpad-proto.git\n94: cd community-launchpad-proto\n95: npm install\n96: ```\n97: \n98: ### Start the dev server\n99: \n100: ```bash\n101: npm run dev\n102: ```\n103: \n104: Open [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080). Hot-module replacement is enabled — file saves are reflected instantly.\n105: \n106: ### Available scripts\n107: \n108: | Script | What it does |\n109: |---|---|\n110: | `npm run dev` | Starts Vite dev server with HMR on port 8080 |\n111: | `npm run build` | Production build |\n112: | `npm run build:dev` | Dev-mode build (useful for debugging) |\n113: | `npm run preview` | Serves the production build locally |\n114: | `npm run lint` | ESLint across all TypeScript/Vue files |\n115: | `npm run format` | Prettier format all files |\n116: \n117: ### Resetting state\n118: \n119: The mock store is **in-memory only**. Any change you make (new post, RSVP, mentor request) lives only for the current browser tab session. A full page reload (`F5` / `⌘R`) restores the seed data exactly as committed.\n120: \n121: ### The walkthrough overlay\n122: \n123: When you first open the app you'll see a guided walkthrough overlay (`src/components/Walkthrough.tsx`). Click **Next** to step through all prototype screens, or click **Skip** to go straight to the home feed. The overlay stores its state in `sessionStorage` so it only shows once per browser tab.\n124: \n125: ### Navigating the prototype\n126: \n127: | Route | What you see |\n128: |---|---|\n129: | `/` | Home feed — posts from all joined Spaces, newest first |\n130: | `/spaces/:spaceId` | Single Space with post list + **New Post** composer |\n131: | `/posts/:postId` | Full post + threaded comments + \"Similar posts\" AI stub |\n132: | `/events` | Event card grid; click **RSVP** to mutate in-memory attendees |\n133: | `/mentors` | Request a mentor + view your current matches |\n134: | `/courses` | Course catalogue stub (real LMS: `frappe/lms`) |\n135: | `/members` | Member directory |\n136: | `/members/:userId` | Member profile — bio, posts, badges |\n137: | `/messages` | DM thread list (Raven prototype) |\n138: | `/messages/:threadId` | Single DM conversation |\n139: | `/notifications` | Notification inbox |\n140: | `/settings` | Full settings panel — notifications, privacy, integrations, AI |\n141: | `/docs` | In-app documentation panel |\n142: \n143: ---\n144: \n145: ## 4. Architecture overview\n146: \n147: ```\n148: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n149: │                   Browser (Vue 3 + Vue Router 4)                     │\n150: │                                                                      │\n151: │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────┐ │\n152: │  │  AppLayout   │  │   Pages /   │  │  Components  │  │  Hooks   │ │\n153: │  │ (nav, side-  │  │   Routes    │  │ PostCard,    │  │ useStore │ │\n154: │  │  bar, shell) │  │ (16 files)  │  │ SentimentBdg │  │ etc.     │ │\n155: │  └──────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────┘ │\n156: │                              │                                       │\n157: │              ┌───────────────▼────────────────┐                     │\n158: │              │     src/mock-data/store.ts      │                     │\n159: │              │  (in-memory reactive store)     │                     │\n160: │              │  seed.ts → typed arrays         │                     │\n161: │              │  types.ts → DocType mirror      │                     │\n162: │              └───────────────────────────────  │                     │\n163: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n164: \n165: Production target (Frappe bench):\n166: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n167: │  frappe/frappe  (platform layer)                    │\n168: │  ├─ frappe/gameplan  (Teams / Spaces / Posts)       │\n169: │  ├─ frappe/lms       (Courses / Lessons / Certs)    │\n170: │  ├─ frappe/raven     (DMs / Channels)               │\n171: │  ├─ frappe/helpdesk  (Support / Safeguarding)       │\n172: │  ├─ frappe/wiki      (Handbook / Policies)          │\n173: │  ├─ frappe/insights  (Analytics)                    │\n174: │  ├─ frappe/eps       (Gamification)                 │\n175: │  └─ fg_companion     (Events, Mentors, AI, Polls)   │\n176: │       ├─ DocTypes: FG Event, FG Mentor Match, …     │\n177: │       ├─ doc_events → sentiment, vector search      │\n178: │       └─ @frappe.whitelist() RPC endpoints          │\n179: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n180: ```\n181: \n182: The Vue frontend talks to Frappe via:\n183: - `GET /api/resource/<DocType>` — list / get\n184: - `POST /api/method/frappe.client.insert` — create\n185: - `PUT /api/resource/<DocType>/<name>` — update\n186: - `POST /api/method/fg_companion.api.<function>` — custom RPC\n187: \n188: ---\n189: \n190: ## 5. User journeys — Mermaid flowcharts\n191: \n192: Each flowchart maps directly to a Gherkin scenario in [`docs/09_GHERKIN_UX_SCENARIOS.md`](docs/09_GHERKIN_UX_SCENARIOS.md) and a production ADR in [`docs/adr/`](docs/adr/).\n193: \n194: ### 5.1 New member onboarding\n195: \n196: ```mermaid\n197: flowchart TD\n198:     A([Visitor lands on /]) --> B{Signed in?}\n199:     B -- No --> C[Social Login / Email OTP\\nFrappe Social Login Key]\n200:     C --> D[Profile setup wizard\\nGP User Profile: bio, image, interests]\n201:     D --> E[Space discovery\\nList of GP Projects by visibility]\n202:     E --> F{Join Spaces}\n203:     F --> G[Home feed populates\\nGP Discussion filtered by joined Projects]\n204:     G --> H[Walkthrough overlay\\nfirst-time guide]\n205:     H --> I([Member is active])\n206:     B -- Yes --> G\n207: ```\n208: \n209: ### 5.2 Posting in a Space\n210: \n211: ```mermaid\n212: flowchart TD\n213:     A([Member opens a Space]) --> B[Space page loads\\n/spaces/:spaceId]\n214:     B --> C[Click 'New Post']\n215:     C --> D[NewPostModal opens\\ntitle + rich text body]\n216:     D --> E{Attach poll?}\n217:     E -- Yes --> F[Poll composer\\nfg_poll DocType]\n218:     E -- No --> G\n219:     F --> G[Submit post\\nPOST GP Discussion]\n220:     G --> H[doc_event: after_insert\\nfg_companion.ai.sentiment.enqueue_score]\n221:     H --> I{Sentiment score\\n>= threshold?}\n222:     I -- Yes --> J[fg_sentiment_label = Needs Attention\\nModeration queue entry]\n223:     I -- No --> K[Post appears in feed\\nranked by recency × reactions]\n224:     J --> K\n225:     K --> L[EPS points awarded\\n+10 for first post]\n226:     L --> M{First post ever?}\n227:     M -- Yes --> N[fg_badge_award: 'First Post' badge]\n228:     M -- No --> O([Done])\n229:     N --> O\n230: ```\n231: \n232: ### 5.3 Mentor match flow\n233: \n234: ```mermaid\n235: flowchart TD\n236:     A([Student visits /mentors]) --> B[Member directory filtered\\nrole = Mentor]\n237:     B --> C[Click 'Request Mentor Match']\n238:     C --> D[POST fg_companion.api.request_mentor\\nFG Mentor Match status = Requested]\n239:     D --> E[Mentor receives\\nNotification Log entry]\n240:     E --> F{Mentor accepts?}\n241:     F -- No --> G[Status = Declined\\nStudent notified]\n242:     F -- Yes --> H[Status = Active\\nfg_mentor_match.on_accept hook]\n243:     H --> I[Raven DM channel created\\nwith system message 'Match accepted on date']\n244:     I --> J[Both parties see\\nMessage Joel / Message Maya button]\n245:     J --> K{Session complete?}\n246:     K -- No --> L([Ongoing mentorship])\n247:     K -- Yes --> M[Status = Completed\\nEPS points for mentor]\n248:     M --> N([Match closed])\n249: ```\n250: \n251: ### 5.4 Event RSVP flow\n252: \n253: ```mermaid\n254: flowchart TD\n255:     A([Member visits /events]) --> B[Event grid loads\\nFG Event list view]\n256:     B --> C[Click event card]\n257:     C --> D{event_type?}\n258:     D -- Teams --> E[fg_live_event\\nprovider = teams\\nMicrosoft Graph join_url]\n259:     D -- Internal --> F[frappe/meet WebRTC room]\n260:     D -- BBB --> G[BigBlueButton room]\n261:     D -- In Person --> H[Physical address shown\\n.ics download]\n262:     E & F & G & H --> I[Click RSVP button]\n263:     I --> J[POST fg_companion.api.rsvp\\nFG Event Attendee upsert]\n264:     J --> K{capacity reached?}\n265:     K -- Yes --> L[Waitlist notification\\nEmail Queue entry]\n266:     K -- No --> M[rsvp_status = Going\\nConfirmation email + .ics]\n267:     M --> N([User sees Going badge on card])\n268: ```\n269: \n270: ### 5.5 Course enrolment & progress\n271: \n272: ```mermaid\n273: flowchart TD\n274:     A([Member visits /courses]) --> B[LMS Course catalogue\\nfrappe/lms]\n275:     B --> C{paid_course?}\n276:     C -- Yes --> D[Paywall lock screen\\nfg_space.paywall_plan]\n277:     D --> E{Subscribed?}\n278:     E -- No --> F[Stripe checkout\\nfrappe/payments]\n279:     F --> G[fg_paywall_grant created\\nStripe webhook]\n280:     E -- Yes --> H\n281:     G --> H[Enrol: LMS Enrollment insert]\n282:     C -- No --> H\n283:     H --> I[Course detail page\\nChapters + Lessons]\n284:     I --> J[Open lesson\\n/courses/:id/lessons/:lessonId]\n285:     J --> K{YouTube video?}\n286:     K -- Yes --> L[YouTube embed\\nshortcode player]\n287:     K -- No --> M[Markdown body renders]\n288:     L & M --> N[Mark lesson complete\\nLMS Course Progress = Complete]\n289:     N --> O{All lessons done?}\n290:     O -- No --> I\n291:     O -- Yes --> P[LMS Certificate generated\\nPDF print format]\n292:     P --> Q[EPS points awarded\\n+100 course completion]\n293:     Q --> R([Certificate in profile])\n294: ```\n295: \n296: ### 5.6 Direct messages (Raven)\n297: \n298: ```mermaid\n299: flowchart TD\n300:     A([User clicks 'Message X']) --> B{DM channel exists?}\n301:     B -- No --> C[Create Raven DM channel\\nRaven Channel insert]\n302:     C --> D[System message: 'Conversation started']\n303:     B -- Yes --> E\n304:     D --> E[/messages/:threadId loads]\n305:     E --> F[Message list renders\\nRaven Message list]\n306:     F --> G[User types message]\n307:     G --> H[POST Raven Message insert]\n308:     H --> I[Real-time update\\nFrappe WebSocket / Frappe Desk]\n309:     I --> J{Other party online?}\n310:     J -- No --> K[Push notification\\nFCM via Frappe Framework]\n311:     J -- Yes --> L[Message appears instantly]\n312:     K & L --> M([Conversation active])\n313:     M --> N{Matched via mentor match?}\n314:     N -- Yes --> O[First system message\\nMatch accepted on date]\n315:     N -- No --> P([Standard DM])\n316: ```\n317: \n318: ### 5.7 Safeguarding & moderation pipeline\n319: \n320: ```mermaid\n321: flowchart TD\n322:     A([New post submitted]) --> B[GP Discussion insert]\n323:     B --> C[doc_event: after_insert\\nfg_companion.ai.sentiment.enqueue_score]\n324:     C --> D{enable_sentiment = 1?}\n325:     D -- No --> E([Post published normally])\n326:     D -- Yes --> F[Background worker\\nONNX sentiment model runs]\n327:     F --> G{neg score >= threshold?}\n328:     G -- No --> H[fg_sentiment_label = Neutral/Positive]\n329:     H --> E\n330:     G -- Yes --> I[fg_sentiment_label = Needs Attention\\nfg_sentiment_score written]\n331:     I --> J[Moderation queue entry\\nfg_moderation_queue row]\n332:     J --> K[Helpdesk ticket auto-opened\\nAssigned to Trusted Reviewer]\n333:     K --> L[Space Admin sees amber badge\\non post card — not visible to members]\n334:     L --> M{Reviewer decision}\n335:     M -- Approve --> N[Status cleared\\nPost remains]\n336:     M -- Reject --> O[Post hidden\\nAuthor notified]\n337:     M -- Edit --> P[Admin edits + approves]\n338:     O --> Q{Author appeals?}\n339:     Q -- Yes --> R[Helpdesk appeal ticket]\n340:     Q -- No --> S([Case closed])\n341:     R --> T([Second review])\n342: ```\n343: \n344: ### 5.8 Paywall / membership gating\n345: \n346: ```mermaid\n347: flowchart TD\n348:     A([User clicks a Space with paywall]) --> B{fg_paywall_grant exists?}\n349:     B -- Yes --> C[Enter Space normally]\n350:     B -- No --> D[Lock screen renders\\nPlan name, price, Subscribe CTA]\n351:     D --> E[Click Subscribe]\n352:     E --> F[Stripe Checkout session\\nfrappe/payments]\n353:     F --> G{Payment success?}\n354:     G -- No --> H[Error shown\\nRetry option]\n355:     G -- Yes --> I[Stripe webhook fires\\n/api/method/fg_companion.api.stripe_webhook]\n356:     I --> J[fg_paywall_grant row inserted\\nuser + space + plan]\n357:     J --> K[User redirected\\ninto Space within 5s]\n358:     K --> C\n359:     C --> L([Member can post, comment, react])\n360:     L --> M{Subscription lapses?}\n361:     M -- Yes --> N[Nightly job revokes grant\\nfg_paywall_grant deleted]\n362:     N --> O[User sees lock screen again\\non next visit]\n363:     M -- No --> L\n364: ```\n365: \n366: ### 5.9 Gamification & badge award\n367: \n368: ```mermaid\n369: flowchart TD\n370:     A([Member action occurs]) --> B{Action type}\n371:     B -- Post created --> C[EPS rule: +10 pts on first Post]\n372:     B -- Comment posted --> D[EPS rule: +5 pts]\n373:     B -- Course completed --> E[EPS rule: +100 pts]\n374:     B -- Mentor session done --> F[EPS rule: +50 pts for mentor]\n375:     C & D & E & F --> G[EPS Energy Point entry created\\nfrappe/eps]\n376:     G --> H[Check fg_badge thresholds]\n377:     H --> I{Threshold crossed?}\n378:     I -- No --> J([Points updated in profile])\n379:     I -- Yes --> K[fg_badge_award row created\\nuser + badge + awarded_at]\n380:     K --> L[Badge graphic shown\\nin profile Achievements section]\n381:     L --> M[Notification: 'You earned First Post badge']\n382:     M --> N([Profile updated])\n383: ```\n384: \n385: ### 5.10 Weekly community digest\n386: \n387: ```mermaid\n388: flowchart TD\n389:     A([Monday 08:00 scheduler fires]) --> B[fg_digest_job runs\\nfrappe scheduler_events]\n390:     B --> C[Query all users\\nwhere digest_opt_in = 1]\n391:     C --> D[For each user: fetch joined Spaces]\n392:     D --> E[Query last 7 days of posts\\nper Space ordered by reaction count]\n393:     E --> F[Top 3 posts per Space selected]\n394:     F --> G[Newsletter template rendered\\nwith signed unsubscribe token]\n395:     G --> H[frappe/newsletter send\\nEmail Queue populated]\n396:     H --> I[User receives email\\nsubject: 'This week in your spaces']\n397:     I --> J{User unsubscribes?}\n398:     J -- Yes --> K[digest_opt_in = 0\\nnever emailed again]\n399:     J -- No --> L([Next week's run])\n400: ```\n401: \n402: ### 5.11 Full platform data flow\n403: \n404: ```mermaid\n405: flowchart LR\n406:     subgraph Browser[\"Browser (Vue 3 + Vue Router 4)\"]\n407:         UI[Pages & Components]\n408:         TQ[Reactive Store]\n409:         UI <--> TQ\n410:     end\n411: \n412:     subgraph FrappeHTTP[\"Frappe HTTP API\"]\n413:         REST[\"/api/resource/…\\nCRUD\"]\n414:         RPC[\"/api/method/…\\nWhitelisted Python\"]\n415:     end\n416: \n417:     subgraph FrappeApps[\"Frappe Bench\"]\n418:         GP[gameplan\\nGP Discussion\\nGP Comment\\nGP Reaction]\n419:         LMS[lms\\nLMS Course\\nLMS Lesson\\nLMS Enrollment]\n420:         Raven[raven\\nRaven Channel\\nRaven Message]\n421:         FGC[fg_companion\\nFG Event\\nFG Mentor Match\\nFG AI Settings]\n422:         Core[frappe/frappe\\nUser, Role, Notification\\nEmail Queue, Job]\n423:     end\n424: \n425:     subgraph AI[\"AI / Workers\"]\n426:         Sent[Sentiment ONNX\\nbackground job]\n427:         Vec[pgvector\\nembeddings]\n428:         Otto[otto agent\\nAI bot]\n429:     end\n430: \n431:     TQ --> REST\n432:     TQ --> RPC\n433:     REST --> GP & LMS & Raven & FGC & Core\n434:     RPC --> FGC\n435:     GP --> Sent\n436:     GP --> Vec\n437:     Raven --> Otto\n438:     Core --> Email[\"Email Queue\\n(digest, events, alerts)\"]\n439:     Core --> Push[\"FCM Push\\n(mobile notifications)\"]\n440: ```\n441: \n442: ---\n443: \n444: ## 6. Project structure\n445: \n446: ```\n447: community-launchpad-proto/\n448: ├── src/\n449: │   ├── views/                    # Vue Router page components\n450: │   │   ├── HomeView.vue          # Home feed (/)\n451: │   │   ├── SpaceView.vue         # Space detail\n452: │   │   ├── PostDetailView.vue    # Full post + comments\n453: │   │   ├── EventsView.vue        # Event grid + RSVP\n454: │   │   ├── MentorsView.vue       # Mentor match flow\n455: │   │   ├── CoursesView.vue       # Course catalogue\n456: │   │   ├── CourseDetailView.vue  # Course detail\n457: │   │   ├── CourseNewView.vue     # New course form\n458: │   │   ├── LessonView.vue        # Lesson player\n459: │   │   ├── MembersView.vue       # Member directory\n460: │   │   ├── MemberDetailView.vue  # Member profile\n461: │   │   ├── MessagesView.vue      # DM thread list\n462: │   │   ├── ThreadView.vue        # DM conversation\n463: │   │   ├── NotificationsView.vue # Notification inbox\n464: │   │   ├── SettingsView.vue      # Full settings panel\n465: │   │   └── DocsView.vue          # In-app docs\n466: │   │\n467: │   ├── components/\n468: │   │   ├── AppLayout.vue         # Sidebar nav + top bar shell\n469: │   │   ├── PostCard.vue          # Feed post card with reactions\n470: │   │   ├── SentimentBadge.vue    # Amber \"Flagged\" badge (AI stub)\n471: │   │   ├── NewPostModal.vue      # Rich post composer dialog\n472: │   │   ├── AppAvatar.vue         # User avatar component\n473: │   │   ├── SidebarItem.vue       # Sidebar nav item\n474: │   │   └── Toggle.vue            # Toggle switch component\n475: │   │\n476: │   ├── mock-data/\n477: │   │   ├── types.ts              # TypeScript shapes — mirror Frappe DocTypes\n478: │   │   ├── seed.ts               # Seeded fictional data (teams, spaces, posts…)\n479: │   │   └── store.ts              # Reactive in-memory store + mock AI functions\n480: │   │\n481: │   ├── data/\n482: │   │   └── store.ts              # Production-ready data store client (Frappe HTTP)\n483: │   │\n484: │   ├── lib/                      # Utilities (cn, lovable-error-reporting…)\n485: │   ├── styles.css                # Tailwind + design tokens\n486: │   ├── main.ts                   # Vue app entry + router setup\n487: │   ├── App.vue                   # Root component\n488: │   └── vue-shims.d.ts            # Vue SFC type declarations\n489: │\n490: ├── docs/\n491: │   ├── 00_OVERVIEW.md                   # This project at a glance\n492: │   ├── 01_SCHEMA_MAPPING_TO_FRAPPE.md   # TS type ↔ Frappe DocType field table\n493: │   ├── 02_WHATS_MOCKED_VS_REAL.md       # What's fake; what's genuinely real\n494: │   ├── 03_PORTING_GUIDE.md              # High-level steps to production\n495: │   ├── 04_FRAPPE_TRANSLATION.md         # Concrete Python, commands, code\n496: │   ├── 05_CIRCLE_TO_FRAPPE_MAPPING.md   # Circle.so feature → Frappe mapping\n497: │   ├── 06_FRAPPE_ECOSYSTEM_TWIN.md      # App-by-app ecosystem breakdown\n498: │   ├── 07_ADR_001_FRAPPE_PLATFORM.md    # Original platform ADR\n499: │   ├── 08_FRAPPE_GAP_ANALYSIS.md        # Gap matrix: ⭐ / 🟡 / 🔴 per feature\n500: │   ├── 09_GHERKIN_UX_SCENARIOS.md       # 12 Gherkin acceptance scenarios\n501: │   ├── 10_FRAPPE_UI_MIGRATION.md        # How to adopt frappe-ui everywhere\n502: │   ├── 11_PROPRIETARY_ALGORITHMS.md     # Algorithm documentation\n503: │   └── adr/\n504: │       ├── ADR-001-frappe-platform.md   # Platform choice\n505: │       ├── ADR-002-direct-messages-raven.md\n506: │       ├── ADR-003-live-events-teams-and-meet.md\n507: │       ├── ADR-004-member-directory-custom.md\n508: │       ├── ADR-005-paywall-gating-custom.md\n509: │       ├── ADR-006-moderation-custom.md\n510: │       ├── ADR-007-polls-custom.md\n511: │       ├── ADR-008-gamification-eps.md\n512: │       ├── ADR-009-mobile-strategy.md\n513: │       ├── ADR-010-ai-otto-raven-bot.md\n514: │       └── ADR-011-community-digest.md\n515: │\n516: ├── fg_companion/                 # Python backend app (Frappe)\n517: │   ├── fg_companion/\n518: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n519: │   │   ├── api.py                # Whitelisted RPC endpoints\n520: │   │   ├── hooks.py              # Frappe lifecycle hooks\n521: │   │   ├── ai/\n522: │   │   │   ├── __init__.py\n523: │   │   │   ├── sentiment.py      # ONNX sentiment analysis\n524: │   │   │   └── vectors.py        # pgvector embeddings\n525: │   │   └── doctype/\n526: │   │       ├── fg_ai_settings/\n527: │   │       ├── fg_event/\n528: │   │       ├── fg_event_attendee/\n529: │   │       └── fg_mentor_match/\n530: │   └── setup.py\n531: │\n532: ├── package.json\n533: ├── vite.config.ts\n534: ├── tsconfig.json\n535: ├── eslint.config.js\n536: └── README.md                     # You are here\n537: ```\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## 7. Pages & routes\n542: \n543: | Route | File | Key components | Frappe target |\n544: |---|---|---|---|\n545: | `/` | `views/HomeView.vue` | PostCard, SentimentBadge | `GP Discussion` list |\n546: | `/spaces/:spaceId` | `views/SpaceView.vue` | PostCard, NewPostModal | `GP Project` + `GP Discussion` filtered |\n547: | `/posts/:postId` | `views/PostDetailView.vue` | Comment thread, reactions, similar posts | `GP Discussion`, `GP Comment`, `GP Reaction` |\n548: | `/events` | `views/EventsView.vue` | Event card grid, RSVP button | `FG Event`, `FG Event Attendee` |\n549: | `/mentors` | `views/MentorsView.vue` | Match request, match card | `FG Mentor Match` |\n550: | `/courses` | `views/CoursesView.vue` | Course card grid | `LMS Course` |\n551: | `/courses/:courseId` | `views/CourseDetailView.vue` | Chapter list, lesson list, enrol | `LMS Course`, `LMS Chapter`, `LMS Enrollment` |\n552: | `/courses/:courseId/lessons/:lessonId` | `views/LessonView.vue` | Lesson player, YouTube embed, progress | `LMS Lesson`, `LMS Course Progress` |\n553: | `/members` | `views/MembersView.vue` | Filterable directory | `User` + `GP User Profile` |\n554: | `/members/:userId` | `views/MemberDetailView.vue` | Profile card, posts, badges | `GP User Profile` |\n555: | `/messages` | `views/MessagesView.vue` | Thread list | `Raven Channel` |\n556: | `/messages/:threadId` | `views/ThreadView.vue` | Message bubbles, send form | `Raven Message` |\n557: | `/notifications` | `views/NotificationsView.vue` | Notification inbox | `Notification Log` |\n558: | `/settings` | `views/SettingsView.vue` | Notifications, Privacy, Integrations, AI, SSO | `FG User Settings`, `FG AI Settings`, `Social Login Key` |\n559: | `/docs` | `views/DocsView.vue` | In-app documentation panel | — |\n560: \n561: ---\n562: \n563: ## 8. Mock data & schema contract\n564: \n565: The file [`src/mock-data/types.ts`](src/mock-data/types.ts) is the **canonical schema contract** between the prototype and the production Frappe backend.\n566: \n567: Every TypeScript interface in that file mirrors a real Frappe DocType field-for-field, verified against the live `.json` files on the `main` branches of `frappe/gameplan` and `frappe/lms`. The mapping is fully documented in [`docs/01_SCHEMA_MAPPING_TO_FRAPPE.md`](docs/01_SCHEMA_MAPPING_TO_FRAPPE.md).\n568: \n569: ### DocTypes mirrored\n570: \n571: | TypeScript type | Frappe DocType | Source app |\n572: |---|---|---|\n573: | `GPTeam` | `GP Team` | frappe/gameplan |\n574: | `GPProject` | `GP Project` | frappe/gameplan |\n575: | `GPDiscussion` | `GP Discussion` | frappe/gameplan |\n576: | `GPComment` | `GP Comment` | frappe/gameplan |\n577: | `GPReaction` | `GP Reaction` | frappe/gameplan |\n578: | `GPUserProfile` | `GP User Profile` | frappe/gameplan |\n579: | `LMSCourse` | `LMS Course` | frappe/lms |\n580: | `LMSChapter` | `LMS Chapter` | frappe/lms |\n581: | `LMSLesson` | `LMS Lesson` | frappe/lms |\n582: | `LMSEnrollment` | `LMS Enrollment` | frappe/lms |\n583: | `LMSCourseProgress` | `LMS Course Progress` | frappe/lms |\n584: | `FGEvent` | `FG Event` | fg_companion (new) |\n585: | `FGEventAttendee` | `FG Event Attendee` | fg_companion (new) |\n586: | `FGMentorMatch` | `FG Mentor Match` | fg_companion (new) |\n587: | `FGAISettings` | `FG AI Settings` | fg_companion (new) |\n588: | `FGUserSettings` | `FG User Settings` | fg_companion (new) |\n589: | `FGDMThread` | `Raven Channel` | frappe/raven |\n590: | `FGDMMessage` | `Raven Message` | frappe/raven |\n591: | `FGNotification` | `Notification Log` | frappe/frappe core |\n592: | `FGSSOProvider` | `Social Login Key` | frappe/frappe core |\n593: \n594: ### What is genuinely real vs mocked\n595: \n596: **Real** (actually mutates state in-memory):\n597: - Creating posts, posting comments, RSVPing to events, requesting mentor matches\n598: - All navigation, URL routing, page composition\n599: - The schema — all TypeScript shapes match real Frappe\n600: \n601: **Mocked** (keyword stubs, not ML):\n602: - `mockSentiment()` in `store.ts` — keyword scorer, not ONNX\n603: - `findSimilarPosts()` in `store.ts` — word-overlap, not pgvector\n604: - Auth — the \"current user\" is hardcoded to `maya` in the store\n605: \n606: See [`docs/02_WHATS_MOCKED_VS_REAL.md`](docs/02_WHATS_MOCKED_VS_REAL.md) for full detail.\n607: \n608: ---\n609: \n610: ## 9. The Frappe DNA — why this stack\n611: \n612: This platform is built on the Frappe Framework. This is a deliberate, reasoned decision documented fully in [`docs/adr/ADR-001-frappe-platform.md`](docs/adr/ADR-001-frappe-platform.md). Key reasons:\n613: \n614: ### 1. One auth, one user, one permission model\n615: Every surface — community posts, courses, DMs, helpdesk tickets, wiki pages — uses the **same `User` row, the same Role system, the same DocPerm model**. No SSO duct tape, no role-sync jobs, no cross-system identity drift.\n616: \n617: ### 2. Data sovereignty\n618: First-generation students are a vulnerable cohort. Their data lives in a single Postgres database on UK-region infrastructure (Civo, Hetzner-eu, AWS eu-west-2). `bench backup` creates a complete dump as one tarball. No vendor is in the data path.\n619: \n620: ### 3. Cost at scale\n621: At 5,000 members, Circle.so Pro is ~6× the cost of self-hosted Frappe. The Frappe stack is open source end-to-end and cost scales with infrastructure, not seats.\n622: \n623: ### 4. Extensibility without forking\n624: All extension of upstream apps (gameplan, lms, raven) happens via:\n625: - **Custom Fields** added from `fg_companion` fixtures\n626: - **`doc_events`** hooks in `fg_companion/hooks.py`\n627: - **New DocTypes** in `fg_companion` only\n628: \n629: No upstream app is ever forked. `bench update` continues to work.\n630: \n631: ### 5. The Circle.so feature map is complete\n632: Every Circle.so feature has a Frappe equivalent. See [`docs/05_CIRCLE_TO_FRAPPE_MAPPING.md`](docs/05_CIRCLE_TO_FRAPPE_MAPPING.md) and the gap analysis in [`docs/08_FRAPPE_GAP_ANALYSIS.md`](docs/08_FRAPPE_GAP_ANALYSIS.md).\n633: \n634: ---\n635: \n636: ## 10. The Circle.so DNA — feature parity map\n637: \n638: | Circle.so feature | Frappe equivalent | Status |\n639: |---|---|---|\n640: | Community / site | Frappe site | ⭐ |\n641: | Space Group | `GP Team` | ⭐ |\n642: | Space | `GP Project` | ⭐ |\n643: | Post | `GP Discussion` | ⭐ |\n644: | Comment | `GP Comment` | ⭐ |\n645: | Emoji reaction | `GP Reaction` | ⭐ |\n646: | Member directory | Custom `fg_member_directory` | 🔨 Build |\n647: | Member profile | `GP User Profile` | ⭐ |\n648: | DMs / Channels | Raven | ⭐ |\n649: | Notifications | Frappe `Notification Log` | ⭐ |\n650: | Search | Frappe FTS5 global search | ⭐ |\n651: | Courses | `frappe/lms` full stack | ⭐ |\n652: | Live events (Teams) | `fg_live_event` + Microsoft Graph | 🔨 Build |\n653: | Live events (internal) | `frappe/meet` WebRTC | 🟡 |\n654: | Polls | `fg_poll` + `fg_poll_vote` | 🔨 Build |\n655: | Paywall / membership | `frappe/payments` + `fg_paywall_grant` | 🟡 |\n656: | Email digest | `frappe/newsletter` + `fg_digest_job` | 🟡 |\n657: | Gamification | `frappe/eps` + `fg_badge` | ⭐ |\n658: | Helpdesk / support | `frappe/helpdesk` | ⭐ |\n659: | Wiki / handbook | `frappe/wiki` | ⭐ |\n660: | Analytics | `frappe/insights` | ⭐ |\n661: | AI moderation | `fg_companion` + ONNX sentiment | 🔨 Build |\n662: | AI bot | Raven AI bot / otto | 🟡 |\n663: | Mobile | Raven mobile + PWA | 🟡 |\n664: | SSO / OAuth2 | Frappe Social Login Key | ⭐ |\n665: | 2FA | Frappe TOTP / Email OTP | ⭐ |\n666: \n667: *⭐ = production-ready Frappe feature · 🟡 = partial/early · 🔨 = build in `fg_companion`*\n668: \n669: ---\n670: \n671: ## 11. Documentation index\n672: \n673: | Document | Purpose |\n674: |---|---|\n675: | [`docs/00_OVERVIEW.md`](docs/00_OVERVIEW.md) | Project at a glance |\n676: | [`docs/01_SCHEMA_MAPPING_TO_FRAPPE.md`](docs/01_SCHEMA_MAPPING_TO_FRAPPE.md) | Field-by-field TS ↔ DocType table |\n677: | [`docs/02_WHATS_MOCKED_VS_REAL.md`](docs/02_WHATS_MOCKED_VS_REAL.md) | What's fake vs genuinely real |\n678: | [`docs/03_PORTING_GUIDE.md`](docs/03_PORTING_GUIDE.md) | High-level 6-step porting recipe |\n679: | [`docs/04_FRAPPE_TRANSLATION.md`](docs/04_FRAPPE_TRANSLATION.md) | Concrete Python, shell commands, code samples |\n680: | [`docs/05_CIRCLE_TO_FRAPPE_MAPPING.md`](docs/05_CIRCLE_TO_FRAPPE_MAPPING.md) | Circle feature → DocType table |\n681: | [`docs/06_FRAPPE_ECOSYSTEM_TWIN.md`](docs/06_FRAPPE_ECOSYSTEM_TWIN.md) | App-by-app ecosystem breakdown |\n682: | [`docs/07_ADR_001_FRAPPE_PLATFORM.md`](docs/07_ADR_001_FRAPPE_PLATFORM.md) | Platform ADR (backward-compat copy) |\n683: | [`docs/08_FRAPPE_GAP_ANALYSIS.md`](docs/08_FRAPPE_GAP_ANALYSIS.md) | Gap matrix per feature |\n684: | [`docs/09_GHERKIN_UX_SCENARIOS.md`](docs/09_GHERKIN_UX_SCENARIOS.md) | 12 acceptance scenarios |\n685: | [`docs/10_FRAPPE_UI_MIGRATION.md`](docs/10_FRAPPE_UI_MIGRATION.md) | Adopting frappe-ui component library |\n686: | [`docs/adr/ADR-001`](docs/adr/ADR-001-frappe-platform.md) through [`ADR-011`](docs/adr/ADR-011-community-digest.md) | All architecture decisions |\n687: \n688: ---\n689: \n690: ## 12. How long to production?\n691: \n692: See [`docs/10_FRAPPE_UI_MIGRATION.md`](docs/10_FRAPPE_UI_MIGRATION.md) for the full build estimate. Summary:\n693: \n694: ### Phase 0 — Infrastructure (Week 1–2)\n695: - Provision Frappe bench on UK-region server\n696: - Install gameplan, lms, raven, helpdesk, wiki, insights, eps, newsletter\n697: - Create `fg_companion` app skeleton + fixtures\n698: - Set up CI/CD (GitHub Actions → staging bench)\n699: \n700: **Deliverable:** live staging site, all upstream apps installed, empty data\n701: \n702: ### Phase 1 — Data layer swap (Week 3–4)\n703: - Replace `src/mock-data/store.ts` with `src/data/store.ts` (Frappe HTTP client)\n704: - Wire real Frappe auth (session cookie + CSRF token)\n705: - Seed staging with real-looking data\n706: \n707: **Deliverable:** prototype talks to real Frappe; all CRUD works end-to-end\n708: \n709: ### Phase 2 — fg_companion DocTypes (Week 5–6)\n710: - FG Event, FG Event Attendee, FG Mentor Match, FG User Settings, FG AI Settings\n711: - Custom Fields: `fg_sentiment_label`, `fg_sentiment_score`, `fg_embedding`, `fg_reviewed_by`\n712: - RPC endpoints: `rsvp()`, `request_mentor()`, `ics_export()`\n713: \n714: **Deliverable:** events, RSVP, mentor match, settings all backed by real DocTypes\n715: \n716: ### Phase 3 — AI features (Week 7–8)\n717: - Sentiment ONNX model in background worker (real, not keyword)\n718: - pgvector for similar discussions (real embeddings)\n719: - Moderation queue wired to Helpdesk\n720: - Safeguarding DM via Raven on sentiment flag\n721: \n722: **Deliverable:** real AI moderation, real vector search\n723: \n724: ### Phase 4 — Build-from-scratch features (Week 9–12)\n725: - Member directory (filterable, opt-in/out)\n726: - Polls (`fg_poll`, `fg_poll_vote`, feed card)\n727: - Gamification visuals (`fg_badge`, `fg_badge_award`)\n728: - Paywall (`fg_paywall_grant`, Stripe webhook, lock screen)\n729: - Community digest (`fg_digest_job`, Newsletter template)\n730: - Microsoft Teams live events (Graph API Server Script)\n731: \n732: **Deliverable:** full Circle.so feature parity\n733: \n734: ### Phase 5 — frappe-ui migration (Week 13–14)\n735: - Swap shadcn/ui components for frappe-ui equivalents\n736: - Apply Frappe design tokens\n737: - Verify WCAG 2.2 AA\n738: \n739: **Deliverable:** unified Frappe design system throughout\n740: \n741: ### Phase 6 — QA, pen-test, go-live (Week 15–16)\n742: - Full Gherkin scenario test pass\n743: - Pen-test fg_companion whitelisted endpoints\n744: - WCAG audit\n745: - Go-live\n746: \n747: ### Total estimate: **14–16 weeks** (one senior full-stack engineer + one Frappe Python developer)\n748: \n749: > If the team already has Frappe experience, Phase 0–2 compress to 3 weeks. The bottleneck is Phase 4 (build-from-scratch features).\n750: \n751: ---\n752: \n753: ## 13. Contributing & branch rules\n754: \n755: This repository is connected to [Lovable](https://lovable.dev). Please **do not** force-push, rebase, amend, or squash commits that have already been pushed — this rewrites history on Lovable's side and will cause the user to lose their project history.\n756: \n757: All commits to the connected branch sync back to Lovable and show up in the editor, so keep the branch in a working state at all times.\n758: \n759: ### Development workflow\n760: \n761: ```bash\n762: # Work on a feature branch\n763: git checkout -b feat/my-feature\n764: \n765: # Make changes, then commit\n766: git add .\n767: git commit -m \"feat: add mentor match request flow\"\n768: \n769: # Push and open a PR\n770: git push origin feat/my-feature\n771: ```\n772: \n773: ### Commit convention\n774: \n775: We use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):\n776: \n777: ```\n778: feat:     new feature or UX flow\n779: fix:      bug fix in prototype behaviour\n780: docs:     documentation only change\n781: style:    formatting, no logic change\n782: refactor: code change that neither fixes nor adds\n783: test:     add or update tests\n784: chore:    build system, tooling\n785: ```\n786: \n787: ---\n788: \n789: *Built with ❤️ for first-generation university students everywhere.*\n790: *Prototype: Vue 3 + Vite 8 + Tailwind. Production target: Frappe Framework.*\n\n(End of file - total 790 lines)\n</content>",
